    "start": 8904862.0,
    "end": 8930705.0,
    "text": "handling it as a balancing act between are we reducing our TDMLs of sediment going down to the Chesapeake Bay in the case of stream restoration, but reducing it by 500 trees, which is a big carbon sink. That's one of the questions that I still feel we need to look at more closely to determine whether there's some middle ground there as it relates to our watershed management."
