    "start": 13063050.0,
    "end": 13103605.0,
    "text": "Uh, thank you for this information. I absolutely I fully support your proposal. It sounds like it's fair. The idea of becoming cost-neutral is good. There's a huge difference between $11,000 and $2,000. So I think raising that is really important. I think the other thing is hopefully the deterrence of abuse of those spaces so that the real equity question is that more drivers can have access to those charging charging stations. My only question was about not including a 15-minute grace period like some of the regional jurisdictions have. Is there— was there consideration for that? Or—"
