    "speaker_source_detail": "AssemblyAI could not identify speaker",
    "start": 14405055.0,
    "end": 14467610.0,
    "text": "Thanks for First off, for doing this, because I think it's— we were looking at a kind of a long agenda there when we got started. [FOREIGN LANGUAGE] On consent, what's the difference between a consent item and a regular discussion item? And I ask that because there are two elements of it. The first is whether the item One is read, and not just read, but explained, so somebody can say, \"Here's what this is,\" so we and others who are listening in will have the benefit of that. And so, that's one element of that. And the second is the element of questions. And when you're doing a regular discussion thing, certainly it's not uncommon to— accommodate a number of questions, and I don't know how that approach actually works here. I'm— well, let me just let you respond to that rather than guessing how that might work."
